reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for price
reviews.reviewText: The fact that you get two charging blocks in the order, They have held up well so far, The two usb-A ports charge decently fast. The usb-C ports really help as well. The block temperature stays consistently about room temp.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works well and a great value.
reviews.reviewText: While there are cheaper chargers out there, charging gear isn't something to cheap out on. These chargers are sturdy and deliver the power as promised. They also remain cool to the touch while some more expensive units overheat a bit. Outstanding value. I'll buy from this company again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It's effective and small
reviews.reviewText: It doesn't charge all devices at 40W all ports add up to 40W. That's fine with me. I just wanted to be able to charge more than one device at a time. And I don't need it in 5 minutes. I like to let it sit and charge a a reasonable rate overnight so I don't fry my battery or my device. In the morning, or just a few hours it's ready. No harm done. No heat issues.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 40W USB C and USB A Charger Block 2 Pack 4 Port
reviews.reviewText: I like the versatility of this charger being able to charge using the C or USB A port. I am currently using the USB A port to charge my iphone. The charger does charge my phone in about 2 hours. However, I noticed that the charger gets hot on both short ends of the charger while charging. Therefore, I will never charge two devices at the same time much less 4. My previous charger never got hot like this one and it was only rated at 20 watts.
